"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-paris-2024-team-gb-gold-medal-rush-continues-3206772\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  It was a fabulous Friday for Team GB as the medals continue to rack up  PARIS -Team GBsurged up theParis 2024medal table with their most successful day yet in the French capital.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 209, \"end\": 215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.5224875899477666, \"rank\": 0.6316862204282657, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Emily Craig and Imogen Grant earnedthe first of three goldson a fantastic Friday by completing their revenge mission in the lightweight double sculls.\", \"from\": 226, \"to\": 376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 226, \"end\": 237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Craig\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emily Craig\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Craig\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Craig\"}, {\"begin\": 242, \"end\": 254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imogen Grant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imogen_Grant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pair missed out on a medal by one-hundredth of a second in Tokyo - a photo finish Craig has had pinned to her wall ever since.\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 441, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999995975486, \"rank\": 4.023891555818926e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 464, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"score\": 0.9999507957154823, \"rank\": 4.9150155996567194e-05, \"text\": \"Craig\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Craig_Dean\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She will now be able to replace it with a happier image as the duo finished comfortably clear of Romania and Greece to continue their remarkable unbeaten run in this cycle.\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 607, \"end\": 614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.983167487746108, \"rank\": 0.016976148941680567, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 619, \"end\": 625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9961760113083624, \"rank\": 0.0038386600152281705, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tokyo was part of our story and this Olympics was the grand finale,\\\" Grant said.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 685, \"end\": 690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999995975486, \"rank\": 4.023891555818926e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 754, \"end\": 759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulysses_S._Grant\", \"score\": 0.9999990384481028, \"rank\": 6.473562165023665e-07, \"text\": \"Grant\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulysses_S._Grant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ulysses_S._Grant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Not every Olympian gets it right on its first try and we did not back in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999668334573, \"rank\": 3.316632538784135e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999995975486, \"rank\": 4.023891555818926e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we have put in so much work and we are much better people this time around.\\\"\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bryony Page continued the British momentum with a landmark gold in women's trampolining.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 1018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 930, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bryony Page\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bryony_Page\"}, {\"begin\": 956, \"end\": 963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9723587263396473, \"rank\": 0.028324325758966394, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 33-year-old, who won silver in Rio and bronze in Tokyo, completed the set in style to become Team GB's first ever Olympic champion in the sport.\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1055, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0675408995379778e-19, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999995975486, \"rank\": 4.023891555818926e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999979417342083, \"rank\": 2.0582701602060764e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She reiterated a long-held desire to perform as part ofCirque du Soleilin the aftermath of her triumph but this is not the end of her Olympic journey.\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1320, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have got more I want to do on trampoline so I will not be going straight away,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1322, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I want to show what my glass ceiling is and break through it.\\\"\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1479, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was more history created against the fitting backdrop of Versailles as Harry Charles followed his father Peter on to the Olympic podium.\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1623, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1544, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 0.9999219608264402, \"rank\": 7.804526408165948e-05, \"text\": \"Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}, {\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.6081494296916137, \"rank\": 0.6442712976673627, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"score\": 0.9865682545137282, \"rank\": 0.013614590989761068, \"text\": \"Peter\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Charles, 25, joined Scott Brash and Ben Maher to guide Team GB to glory in team showjumping - an event he watched from the sidelines as a 13-year-old atLondon 2012when his dad won gold.\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1625, \"end\": 1632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.6081494296916137, \"rank\": 0.6442712976673627, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 1645, \"end\": 1656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Brash\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scott Brash\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Brash\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Brash\"}, {\"begin\": 1661, \"end\": 1670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Maher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Maher\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Maher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Maher\"}, {\"begin\": 1680, \"end\": 1687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999979417342083, \"rank\": 2.0582701602060764e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In doing so, they are the first father-son combination to win Olympic gold for Team GB since 1948 - rowers Dickie and Charles Burnell (1908) the last to do it.\", \"from\": 1812, \"to\": 1971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1891, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999979417342083, \"rank\": 2.0582701602060764e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1930, \"end\": 1945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Burnell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charles Burnell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Burnell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_Burnell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Harry Charles must surely be the first to have won alongside his dad's teammates, the triumphant quartet in London being Maher, Brash, Peter Charles and Nick Skelton, in a slightly different format.\", \"from\": 1973, \"to\": 2175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1983, \"end\": 1990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.6081494296916137, \"rank\": 0.6442712976673627, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 2085, \"end\": 2091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999077267645, \"rank\": 7.76108871843893e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 2112, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"score\": 0.9865682545137282, \"rank\": 0.013614590989761068, \"text\": \"Peter\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Griffin\"}, {\"begin\": 2118, \"end\": 2125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"score\": 0.6081494296916137, \"rank\": 0.6442712976673627, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_II_of_England\"}, {\"begin\": 2130, \"end\": 2142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Skelton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nick Skelton\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Skelton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Skelton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Harry said: \\\"They are both my heroes, guys I have looked up to since I started riding.\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To be on the podium with them, my inner, younger self is freaking out a little bit.\\\"\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Four more medals were banked either on or in the water.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2405, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's pair could not quite match the women's success as rowers Ollie Wynne-Griffith and Tom George, who led from almost start to finish, were edged out by Croatia's Martin and Valent Sinkovic.\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2498, \"end\": 2508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_George\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom George\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_George\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_George\"}, {\"begin\": 2565, \"end\": 2572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9985060370425948, \"rank\": 0.0013239837044231987, \"text\": \"Croatia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2575, \"end\": 2581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"score\": 0.999995951642186, \"rank\": 4.048223067314016e-06, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martin_Crane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ben Proud broke his Olympic duck at the third attempt with a thrilling silver in the men's 50m freestyle whileDuncan Scottfinished runner-up to face of the GamesLeon Marchandin the men's 200m individual medley, the Frenchman claiming a remarkable fourth gold.\", \"from\": 2604, \"to\": 2863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2604, \"end\": 2613, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Proud\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ben Proud\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Proud\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Proud\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jack Laugher and Anthony Harding, meanwhile, had to master the toughest dive in the world to win an Olympic bronze medal in the 3m synchro.\", \"from\": 2865, \"to\": 3004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2865, \"end\": 2877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jack Laugher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Laugher\"}, {\"begin\": 2882, \"end\": 2897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Harding_(archaeologist)\", \"score\": 0.8333269169617231, \"rank\": 0.19999999999996818, \"text\": \"Anthony Harding\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Harding_(archaeologist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anthony_Harding_(archaeologist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a fourth Olympic medal for Laugher and Harding's first on debut.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the first day of athletics, Josh Kerr, Keely Hodgkinson andDina Asher-Smithwere among those to ease through their opening rounds but Morgan Lake failed to make the high jump final.\", \"from\": 3078, \"to\": 3261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3109, \"end\": 3113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Ashworth\", \"score\": 0.989431135473694, \"rank\": 0.010606966369551106, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Ashworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Ashworth\"}, {\"begin\": 3120, \"end\": 3136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 3214, \"end\": 3225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Lake\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Morgan Lake\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Lake\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Lake\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am still not quite sure what went on,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was maybe thinking ahead to Sunday too much, focusing on the final before I even got through qualifying.\\\"\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was British disappointment, meanwhile, in the BMX racing.\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3435, \"end\": 3442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9723587263396473, \"rank\": 0.028324325758966394, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 3477, \"end\": 3487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9909109745017078, \"rank\": 0.009172393617923014, \"text\": \"BMX racing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Defending champion Beth Shriever cruised through the heats but got squeezed out early on in the final and came home eighth, while Kyle Whyte - who won silver in Tokyo - was taken to hospital after a crash in his semi-final.\", \"from\": 3489, \"to\": 3712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3619, \"end\": 3629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Powys_Whyte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kyle Whyte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Powys_Whyte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kyle_Powys_Whyte\"}, {\"begin\": 3650, \"end\": 3655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.999999995975486, \"rank\": 4.023891555818926e-09, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch every moment of Paris 2024 live only on discovery+, the streaming home of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3714, \"to\": 3807, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3746, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.464075472064475e-19, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Impartial news + intelligent debate  All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 3809, \"to\": 3866, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 Associated Newspapers Limited.\", \"from\": 3867, \"to\": 3904, \"entities\": []}]}"